Tianjin Capital, China Environment Stocks Gain on Government Plan

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-10-21T02:58:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-21/tianjin-capital-china-environment-stocks-gain-on-government-plan.html
Tianjin Capital Environmental
Protection Group Co. led gains of China environmental-related
stocks after the government said it will increase investment to
the environmental protection industry.  Tianjin Capital jumped 4.8 percent to 5.50 yuan as of 10:19
a.m. in  Shanghai , set for its biggest rise since Aug. 25. The
stock gained 2.8 percent to HK$1.85 in  Hong Kong , the first
increase in six days. Sound Environmental Resources Co. added
2.2 percent to 25.09 yuan in Shenzhen. Shanghai Chengtou Holding
Co. added 3.3 percent to 6.29 yuan.  China plans to include environmental protection investment
in the annual fiscal budgets at all levels of government,
according to a statement posted on the governmentâ€™s website
yesterday following a meeting of the cabinet, headed by Premier
 Wen Jiabao .   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
